I enjoyed my lectures with Lisa. Her lectures were engaging, interesting, and insightful. Lisa is one of the few professors who seems to focus on actually teaching her students, and them actually learning something, rather than just dishing out test after test. Immature students take a lack of a final exam as a reason to skip lectures. Their loss.

Attendance on lecture is worth 10% of the final mark, which should be an easy mark but professor Peden has made it difficult by giving the most boring lectures ever. I barely learn anything from the lecture. The tutorial is pretty helpful since unlike Peden, my TA is actually teaching us course related content.

She makes me regret my major and I'm 100% sure she tells her TAs not to give out high marks because she knows her classes are pathetically easy. It's not my fault the content is at a 5th grade level. Avoid at all costs.
She is one of the best profs I have had. She is caring and funny and has a clear grading criteria

Every instructor needs to take a page from Liz Peden! She knows how to teach! She makes excellent use of class time and her TAs are well selected! I had low interest taking this course but enjoyed it in the end. Underrated Professor for sure!!
